19/09/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The country assumed leadership of the UN General Assembly on Tuesday (September 18th), represented by Srgjan Kerim.
He opened the 62nd session of the Assembly with a call for all members to ensure the organisation is positioned to handle the world's most pressing issues.
Kerim said his priorities would be climate change, development financing, the Millennium Development Goals, management reform, and fighting terrorism and poverty.
(UN web site, A1, AP, Makfax, MIA - 18/09/07)
